column5: I think it was more fun taking photos than fishing for these fish!! Check it out.           Then I took pics from another angle. It revealed a surprise.      A closer look at the photo above... revealed this,..next photo below!!   What's he doing in there? Does he think he's a salmon as well?      Well that's all, too bad it clouded over. With out the bit of sun I would't have been able to even spot the rainbow. All the fish look black.  dsn
WOW!!! Superb shots DSN!!!
Just a normal, healthy guy lookin' for a little 'strange'.
Wow, neat.  How many tries did it take them to make it?  Joey
The surprise fish looks like a Brown to me. Lots of spots and darker color for a rainbow.  If so he or she is doing just what the salmon are doing, going to spawn.
very cool
They were actually swimming/jumping away from this...    ZAP!
Really cool pics.
awesome pics
AWESOME!
Great stuff! I agree, watching them is way more fun than fishing for them at this time of year!
Very nice shots there!
Love the pics., thanks for showing
Great shots dsn. Much better to watch them do their thing!  Well done for spotting the trout in amongst those salmon.  007
Great shots DSN, thanks for posting them.
Great shots, I was also watching the Salmon and Rainbows do there thing in Kagawong a couple weekends ago. Awesome to see nature first hand.
those r amazing shots man, thnx
Great pics!  I'll second Paul, gotta be a Brownie....
Beauty shots DSN

Very kewl!  I stop and look every time I'm in those parts...  I was actually volunteering with Ontario Streams back in 1999, when they notched the first wear there.  We knotched the last wear in 2004 at Cruikshank Park.  Makes it all worth while when I look at those shots...  Let's hope those fish reach suitable spawning grounds and we get a natural return from them.  cheers! HD
great pics dsn!
Very nice shots !  Thanks for sharing. Yes .. definitely a brown ... the rainbows will be coming soon too though
nice pictures, thanks for sharing.
